This paper deals with caching popular contents in vehicle-to-vehicle (V2V) communication networks, which is a topic related to networked systems (cs.NI) and information theory (cs.IT). The proposed spatio-temporal caching strategy is based on identifying temporal graph motifs, which is a technique used in graph theory and social network analysis (cs.SI). The paper also discusses the importance of effective content dissemination and traffic management, which are topics related to computer networks and security (cs.CR) and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC).
